.TH w_querywindowpos 3w "Version 1, Release 4" "W Window System" "WLIB FUNCTIONS"
.SH NAME
w_querywindowpos() \- return window position
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <Wlib.h>
.sp
\fBshort w_querywindowpos(WWIN *\fIwin\fB, short\fI effective\fB,
short *\fIx0\fB, short *\fIy0\fB);
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.I w_querywindowpos()
 asks for either the working area
.B (effective
= 0) or total area
.B (effective
= 1) position of a window.
